[[File:Schlern von Rotwand am Ritten.jpg|thumb|The journal ''Der Schlern'' was named after the mountain [[Schlern]].]] '''''Der Schlern''''' (full [[German language|German]] title: ''Der Schlern – Zeitschrift für Südtiroler Landeskunde''; {{lang-en|The Schlern – Magazine for South Tyrolean Regional Studies}}) is a German-language [[wikt:Monthly|monthly]] for the study of science, research, art and culture related to [[South Tyrol]].
First published on 1 January 1920, it is named after the [[Schlern]], a characteristic mountain in the [[Dolomites]]. In 1938, it was forbidden by the [[Italian Fascism|Italian fascist regime]] as part of their [[Italianization of South Tyrol]] programme, but permitted again by the [[Allies of World War II|allied]] administration in 1946.<ref>Cf. Obermair. ''Umbrüche – Übergänge – Chancen'', op. cit., pp. 273–74.</ref>
The [[magazine]] is currently published in [[Bolzano]] by Athesia (formerly ''Tyrolia'').
