[[File:Cadell iona.jpg|thumb|''Iona'' by [[Francis Cadell (artist)|Francis Cadell]] (1883–1937), exhibited at the Portland Gallery]]
'''Portland Gallery''' is an [[art gallery]] in central [[London]], [[England]].<ref name="slad">{{cite web| url=http://www.slad.org.uk/art-dealers/d/portland-gallery/32100 | title=Portland Gallery | publisher=[[The Society of London Art Dealers]] | accessdate=25 October 2016 }}</ref>

Founded in 1984 by Tom Hewlett, the gallery displays modern [[British art|British]] and [[Contemporary art|Contemporary paintings]]. A particular specialization is the work of [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[colorist|colourists]] [[Samuel Peploe]], [[Francis Cadell (artist)|Francis Cadell]], [[George Leslie Hunter]], and [[John Duncan Fergusson]], and their immediate followers, including [[Anne Redpath]] and John Maclauchlan Milne. The gallery also hosts the [[estate (law)|estate]] [[art collection|collections]] of Cadell, Maclauchlan Milne, and [[Edward Seago]].

Among [[contemporary painter]]s and [[sculptor]]s, the gallery has displayed works by Archie Forrest, Gary Bunt, Paul Rafferty, [[Nicholas Hely Hutchinson]], Gordon Mitchell, Oliver Akers Douglas, and David Spiller.<ref name="slad" />

The gallery exhibits at the [[London Art Fair]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.londonartfair.co.uk/exhibitor/portland-gallery/ | title=Portland Gallery | publisher=[[London Art Fair]] | location=UK | accessdate=25 October 2016 }}</ref> It is located at 3 Bennet Street in London, close to [[The Ritz Hotel, London|The Ritz Hotel]].

